gomodel:SYNGO_1480  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using immunocytochemistry and electron microscopy, the referenced study established that in the rat prelimbic prefrontal cortex, most 5-HT2a receptors are located within postsynaptic structures, predominantly on proximal and distal dendritic shafts. 5-HT2a receptor immunoreactivity was observed in 325 identifiable structures. Of these, 73% were postsynaptic profiles that were composed of either dendritic shafts (58%) or dendritic spine heads and necks (42%).\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Four naive adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Hilltop Laboratory Animals, Scottsdale, PA, USA) were used..." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1480" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

